description:
Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Skull Kid and the Demon Mask
  • Chapter 2: Link the Deku Scrub
  • Chapter 3: The Happy Mask Shop
  • Chapter 4: Odolwa: God of Woodfall
  • Chapter 5: The Monster of Snowhead
  • Chapter 6: The Great Bay
  • Chapter 7: Anji and Kafei
  • Chapter 8: Stop the Moon!!
  • Chapter 9: Fierce Deity Link
  • Original Side Story
name: Majora's Mask
Oracle of Ages

description:
Appearances can be deceiving. There is trouble in Tokyo as a mysterious terrorist organization called ALICE plots against the government. Just as the police are tasked to bring these men to justice, they are given a "secret weapon", who happens to be a young girl, with a mysterious past, named Kasumi Asakura. She may look innocent, but walks softly and carries a big gun.

----------

When you're a cop on the cold, hard streets of Tokyo, the only thing keeping you alive may be a sweet, innocent teenage schoolgirl... as long as she's a well-trained renegade assassin.

When the ALICE organization declares war on the city's police, the high stripes need Officer Kyoji Kido, a man whose gun has a kick that can rip the arm off most men. He's been teamed up with Kasumi Asakura, who certainly knows how to handle a gun, even his. But Asakura's mysterious past leaves a lot about her to distrust.

From GTO creator Tohru Fujisawa comes this hard-boiled tale filled with firefights, love bites and schoolgirls packing lots of heat!
name: Vol. 1

description: Kyoji Kido, a Japanese police officer, and his teenage partner, Kasumi Asakura, are assigned to bodyguard the Assistant Commissioner of the Japanese Police Force, who is a potential target of ALICE, a Japanese mercenary organization responsible for terrorist attacks. Kasumi must save the Assistant Commissioner's life from two ex-comrades working in ALICE. If that wasn’t enough, ALICE has a special weapon--EIN about to wake up...
name: Vol. 2

description: Kasumi and Kido, now reunited, still have a lot of work ahead of them. They might be able to confront Hayato and Kai, but they are only arms of a much larger organization, and only pawns in a much larger war. When ZERO finally lets himself be known, he will be on international terrorist who won’t be in the mood to negotiate. And when the secret of EIN is revealed, it may not matter at all what Kasumi and Kido do to try to stop ZERO.
name: Vol. 3

description: The terrorists have left Tokyo alone for two years, until a gunman takes the teachers hostage at Kasumi’s school in just one of a string of gun violence incidents throughout Tokyo. Someone is distributing guns to anyone who posts death threats on a certain website--and all the guns are engraved with a very familiar rose emblem! ALICE is on the move again!
name: Vol. 4

description: Sixteen-year-old Kasumi's quest to help the police take down the terrorist organization that raised her, ALICE, has led them to a gang in Ikebukuro called Black Rose that's been distributing guns throughout the city as part of a sinister plan to kill thousands. When Kasumi gets duped into going to an underground construction site, she gets captured by ALICE and forced to witness indiscriminate mass murders! The horror of it drives her into despair and rage--and EIN, the monstrous personality she had been suppressing for years, finally awakens. The heart-racing conclusion is here!
name: Vol. 5

description: On a world with no women, the surviving men have reinvented females in the form of androids called Marionettes. Normal marionettes are built to serve men and are limited in their actions and emotions until a poor boy named Otaru Mamiya finds a special Saber Marionette named Lime. With war close at hand and two more Saber Marionettes at his side, his life takes a turn for the better as he unlocks the emotions that may hold the key to the salvation of mankind.
name: Vol. 1

description: Otaru and Saber Marionettes Lime, Cherry, and Bloodberry go on a mission to destroy the main computer of Gartland. Along the way, they meet up with the Saber Dolls whose loyalties lie with Faust, Gartlands evil overlord. The Saber Dolls prove to be an equal match for the Marionettes due to their maiden circuits and the would be heroes are left in disarray after a prolonged battle, their goal of destroying the computer just out of reach.
name: Vol. 2

description: In an attempt to defeat Otaru and return to Faust, Tiger tries to follow Zoringen's plan to destroy Otaru with a kiss. She is unable to bring herself to kiss Otaru, and comes to the realization that she belongs to Faust and Faust alone. This realization doesn't do her much good, as she, Panta, and Luchs are struck by a plasma attack during an attack on Otaru and company. Otaru is kind enough to revive them, but their memory circuits are fried and they get the Saber Doll equivalent of amnesia. In the meantime, supplies from Gartlant are late and Zoringen is reduced to thievery in order to survive.
name: Vol. 3

description: The Saber Dolls (Tiger, Lynx and Panther) regain their memories as the villainous Faust is brought back to life. The Saber Marionettes (Lime, Cherry and Bloodberry) leave Otaru and Japoness, sending Otaru into a tailspin of depression. Meanwhile, Faust attacks Japoness to find Lorelei, the one-and-only real woman known to man. Ieyasu tells the tale of Lorelei. The Maiden Circuits resonate with Lorelei's grief as the capsule containing her is brought to Gartland , and the final battle begins.
name: Vol. 4

description: Welcome to Terra 2, a wild world without women. The surviving men have created Marionettes--curvy androids in fleshy female forms--to serve man's every desire...outside of the bedroom, that is. A few special Marionettes are equipped with Maiden Circuits--devices inside them that simulate the emotions and memories of real women. In short, they are machines...with souls! Otaru Mamiya has been charged with caring for three such Marionettes--Lime, Cherry, and Bloodberry--and together, they've protected their homeland, Japoness, from the aggressive country known as Gartland. In this volume--the climactic conclusion to the SMJ manga series--Otaru and the Saber Marionettes must invade Gartland to retrieve Lorelei--the one-and-only real woman in the world--from the evil Lord Faust...or die trying!
name: Vol. 5

description: Who is the fantastic thief Saint Tail who dazzles the cops with her magic? Asuka Jr. sets out to stop her from stealing the Blue Meteor, never suspecting that she is someone already close to him. But what is Saint Tail's real purpose with the beautiful sapphire, and is she truly just a criminal?
name: Vol. 1

description: Saint Tail and Meimi have a new rival for Asuka Jr. - and her name is Lina Takamiya, the mayor's daughter. Lina sets out to catch Saint Tail so she can capture the heart of the single-minded sleuth.
name: Vol. 2

description: Saint Tail has to outwit two inquisitive detectives these days--Lina and Asuka Jr. In this, the third volume of the popular magical comedy, she deals with a jewel in a hedgehog, damaging photos, and a magic mirror!
name: Vol. 3

description: Asuka is beginning to suspect that Meimi and Saint Tail may be one and the same, as clues keep piling up. Saint Tail, on the other hand, grapples with her own feelings for the young detective, and even considers giving up the ruse and telling Asuka her secret identity.
name: Vol. 4

description: Seika City has borrowed the Swan, a famous sculpture, from Sakuraoka City, but Mayor Okajima of Sakuraoka plans to steal it and pin the blame on Saint Tail and Seika City. This can't be good news for our intrepid thief...but she always manages to find a way...
name: Vol. 5

description: By day, Meimi Haneoka is an ordinary student at St. Paulia's middle school, but by night she is Saint Tail, the magical thief who steals back treasures for their rightful owners. For months now, the aspiring young detective Asuka Jr. has been hot on St. Tail's trail. At first, he thought he was doing it for justice, then because it was a game with a worthy foe, but now he's beginning to realize that his feelings may be more complex. Of course, he's also got feelings for Meimi (not realizing that she and the magical thief are one in the same). Can he finally confess his love and, if so, for which girl?
name: Vol. 6

description: "Forgive me, Lord, for the tricks up my sleeves!" By day, Meimi Haneoka is an ordinary schoolgirl, struggling with boys and homework. But by night, she pulls off fantastic heists as the mysterious thief Saint Tail! In this final volume of the landmark series, manga artist extraordinare Megumi Tachikawa shares some of the initial character sketches for her magical Saint Tail creations. Tachikawa-san says these are the same pencil sketches that she showed to her editor with a pounding heart long ago. And, for the first time ever, she finally shares the secret of Saint Tail's origins. Don't miss Saint Tail's sensational swan song!
name: Vol. 7

description:
The fearsome foursome continue their journey west towards Shangri-La, encountering new challenges and new adventures along the way. Their legend precedes them, but not always in the way one might expect. The Minus Wave that apparently drove all the youkai in the land mad looks like it might have missed one, as Sanzo, Gojyo, Hakkai and Goku meet a lone guardian and the band of children he cares for. Fear and misunderstanding run throughout this particular leg of the journey, including between the members of the Sanzo group!

Chapter Titles

  • Act.1: Run
  • Act.2: Snow Drop 1
  • Act.3: Snow Drop 2
  • Act.3.5: 3 Years Ago
  • Act.4: Death Match
name: Vol. 1

description: The journey continues as Sanzo faces off against his evil doppelganger. The progress westward is held up continually as new villains surface, and an old foe makes a new appearance. Yaone and Dokugakuji drag our heroes out of a river just in time for the new and improved Kougaiji to come along to kick some butt. His soul replaced with unbelievable strength, Kou now proves to be a challenge for even Goku. While his companions wrestle with corporeal demons, Sanzo must face some of his own inner fears.
name: Vol. 2

description: When Goku loses all ability to fight Kougaiji, Sanzo and the others show up to fight for him. Yaone and Dokugakuji aren't sure of what to do at first, because the current Kougaiji isn't the same Kougaiji they swore allegiance to, but eventually their loyalty helps Kougaiji overcome his brainwashing. Also, we begin to see the explanation of many of the characters past as Sanzo and company celebrate the one year anniversary of their journey west.
name: Vol. 3

description: New troubles and new characters are introduced in this exciting installment of Saiyuki Reload! Sanzo and Goku become even closer while Hakkai and Gojyo's friendship is tested. As the fearsome foursome continue on in their latest adventure, what will happen when they are faced with a new kind of enemy?
name: Vol. 4

description: A group of youkai advance upon Goku, Hakkai, and Gojyo. To stop the onslaught against Sanzo and company, Hazel and Gat show up to exterminate the attackers. Our heroes begin to disagree with one another when youkai children join the fray! Is it morally wrong to slay those that are trying to kill you--even if they are children?!
name: Vol. 5

description: Ukoku/Ni Jianyi returns! The renegade Sanzo priest tells Hazel of the Great Sage Equalling Heaven, how he is the most dangerous youkai in the land, and that the Sage is traveling with the Sanzo party. Hazel now has to make a new decision: Is his personal quest worth sacrificing a new friend? Meanwhile, the Sanzo party ends up in a mysteriously prosperous and youkai-free village. What kind of deal has the village headman made to maintain their safety? And what will happen when the fearsome foursome get involved?!
name: Vol. 6

description: Goku's life hangs in the balance after the attack of an unknown enemy, and Sanzo, Gojyo, and Hakkai are at a total loss... Until Hakkai suggests they pull off Goku's diadem. But no one seems ready for what is about to happen: Facing Goku in youkai form is more than they bargained for--and it may even cost one member of the party their own sanity!
name: Vol. 7

description: Sanzo has gone one way, and the rest of the party another, until they end up on opposite sides of a small mountain. The tension between the peaceful town of Youkai and the humans guarding the oasis has come to a head, and when things boil over, it's anyone's guess whose side the gang will join!
name: Vol. 8

description: Ukoku is back and creepier than ever, and it's going to be the Seiten sutra vs. the Muten if Sanzo has his way. Meanwhile, Hazel's past is revealed, along with his own knowledge of Ukoku and the Muten sutra. Let the exciting showdown begin!
name: Vol. 9

description: Ensign Ogami has only just begun his first assignment, and he's already considering handing in his resignation! Punching tickets at the theater doesn't seem to be furthering his goal of defending Tokyo from demonic invaders, but the employees of the Imperial Theater are more than they seem, and Manager Yoneda is no exception. When the girls suit up for their first major battle against the demon steam suits, they will find their enemies are quite a bit tougher than initially anticipated!
name: Vol. 2

description: The action heats up both on stage and on the streets of Tokyo. Sakura's first starring role in the theater is a complete disaster, fortunately Sakura can still hold more than her own on the battlefield! Demon invaders and sinister forces provide quite a challenge for our talented troupe, but it's nothing that a little teamwork and fighting spirit can't handle and there's always time for a little romantic intermission, though. Love may be blossoming on the battlefield, in spite of all odds!
name: Vol. 3

description: Ensign Ogami is hurt from his attempt to rescue a child from Setsuna. Nonetheless, he presses the Flower Team into rehearsing a new play, Cinderella. A confident Ogami tries to cheer up Maria and help her get over the nightmares. Maria decides to seeks revenge for her lover! Who will protect Maria from her own foolish ambitions?
name: Vol. 4

description: When Rasetsu and Setsuna's brother ask Satan to bring Setsuna back from the dead, Satan agrees to do so on one condition. Rasetsu must destroy the Imperial Fighting Troupe. Rasetsu plots an attack on the Kobus with his spirit-operated weapon. The Imperial Fighting Troupe is about to lose all its powers! Meanwhile, Iris has the power to stop Rasetsu, but will her emotions get in her way?
name: Vol. 5

description: Iris and her healing abilities step into the playing field to help the Imperial Fighting Troupe to victory. Meanwhile, Kanna and Sunmire are in the midst of a bitter feud over the mess they left behind on their stage performance when they are assigned along with Ogami to investigate what looks like a haunted house.
name: Vol. 6

description: Three from the Flower Troupe are sent on another mission--this time, in the creepy interior of a haunted house! But with Sumire and Kanna already at odds with each other, working as a team to beat the vengeful spirit behind the chaos may take a miracle!
name: Vol. 7

description:
In a school where martial arts are standard curriculum, Samurai Girl Ryoko is the top fighter and most popular student around...or is she? Things change when the uncouth fighter Shizuma Kusanagi transfers in from Kansai. He may not have the grace of Ryoko, but his amazing fighting abilities could make him the most dominant martial artist at Daimon High. Principal Todo encourages rivalry between the competitors, setting up a dangerous 'K-Fighting' tournament where even the teachers can join in and settle once-and-for-all just who is the top dog on campus.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Enter the Samurai Girl!
  • Chapter 2: Shizuma Goes Ashore
  • Chapter 3: A Great Woman
  • Chapter 4: The Duel, Official Announcement
  • Chapter 5: The Duel, Fin
  • Chapter 6: A Pack of Wolves
  • Chapter 7: Elegy of a Teacher and Student
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Samurai Girl: Real Bout High School

description:
Samurai Girl Ryoko is set on breaking bones as a Samurai Nurse, but there are plenty of challengers ready to knock her out for good! And with teachers entering the ring to duke it out, all bets are off. Who has time for homework when there's a battle to catch?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 8: Elegy of a Teacher and Student, Again
  • Chapter 9: Elegy of a Teacher and Student, the final Chapter
  • Chapter 10: Daimon's Moon and Sun
  • Chapter 11: You and Me, I Need You
  • Chapter 12: Hitomi's Records of a Bloody Storm
  • Chapter 13: A Subtle Strange Occurrence, Tatsuya Shishikura
  • Chapter 14: Blue Spring, Blue Spring
  • Chapter 15: That's Suddenly... Abruptly
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Samurai Girl: Real Bout High School

description:
In a school where martial arts are standard curriculum and disputes are settled by officially recognized duels, Ryoko is kicking butt and taking names. But this otherwise innocent high school girl is in for the fight of the year when she is challenged to a K-Fight by Azumi. The whole school soon becomes their battlefield in the biggest grudge match yet.

Contents

  • Bewildered Swordsman
  • The Rematch - Part 1
  • The Rematch - Part 2
  • The Rematch - Part 3
  • Bye-Bye
  • Moment of Parting, Day of Resolution
  • Wartime in Spring
  • Side Stories: Real Bout High School Short Stories
name: Vol. 3

volume.name: Samurai Girl: Real Bout High School

description:
Daimon High School's student council president Isozaki asks martial arts expert and fellow classmate Ryoko to collaborate on an effort to sweep the streets clean of troublemaking scum. But his hidden agenda is clear: he wants to expand the K-Fight program beyond the school's campus, and does so by pitting Ryoko and four other women warriors against Shizuma and his band of brawny brawlers. Surprisingly, Ryoko not only accepts the challenge but agrees to head the group of lady fighters as well, hoping the experience helps her attain her ultimate goal of becoming a great woman. The battle of the sexes is, literally, at hand.

Contents

  • The Call of the Streets
  • How the Fire Tiger and Shock Wave Wolf Learned to Negotiate
  • Shinsengumi, Forward!!
  • A Peaceful Moment After the Battle
  • A Fighting Debutante's Morning, A Friendly Debauchee's Afternoon
  • The One-Eyes Saints
  • Sword to Sword, Ninja to Ninja
  • The Kinds of Days That are Poison for the Soul
name: Vol. 4

volume.name: Samurai Girl: Real Bout High School

description:
Ryoko's climactic fight with Azumi has brought about a change in her outlook of life. Training harder than she ever has before brings forth her hidden talents and she runs out of worthy opponents in short order. However, there is one man who is strong enough to take her on and Ryoko must once again think of a new strategy to overcome the odds.

Contents

  • Episode 29: Losing Sight/Missing Girls
  • Episode 30: Gathering in Dragon Land
  • Episode 31: The Attack Begins, Momoi vs. Taiho, Part 1
  • Episode 32: A Breathtaking Match, Momoi vs. Taiho, Part 2
  • Episode 33: The Gimmick Castle and the Shadow Castle, Part 1
  • Episode 34: The Gimmick Castle and the Shadow Castle, Part 2
  • Episode 35: The Gimmick Castle and the Shadow Castle, Part 3
name: Vol. 5

volume.name: Samurai Girl: Real Bout High School

description:
The decadent Daimon High School spectacular will be concluded mano y mano in a group of magnificent melees and explosive exchanges: After stopping Project Z, Ryoko loses her memory; the battle between "Shinsen-gumi" and "G-gumi" goes to the second round; and the battle of Ryoko vs Shizuma just might go the distance. Nobody pulls a punch in the no-holds-barred final installment of this butt-kicking-and-name-taking series!

Contents

  • The Shadow Trick
  • The Edges of the Battlefield
  • Wolves
  • Wild Dog Rumble
  • The Wounds of Time
  • My Only Opponent
  • Traveling to the Final Match
  • Ryoko Mitsurugi Versus Shizuma Kusanagi
  • ...And the Winner is...
  • The Final Episode
name: Vol. 6

volume.name: Samurai Girl: Real Bout High School

description: The drama isn’t limited to the stage! The day of the Club Presentation Assembly arrives, but when an old enemy from Fukurou's past appears bent on revenge, the Drama Club and their play are put in jeopardy. During the mayhem, Ayame and Fukurou use their womanly charms on Yoichi that will leave him lying on the ground, literally! Things get even more heated up when the deadly sisters of assassins-turned-ramen-delivery-girls Tsubasa and Angela come with loads of weapons at the ready!
name: Vol. 6

description: Shima is a jack-of-all-trades who can solve any problem that's presented to him. When he's approached by Kaori, a super-hot teenage model who's being followed by a mysterious figure known as "The Snowman," the two team up to catch the stone-cold stalker in the act. One thing's for sure: When you hire this hot duo, your satisfaction is guaranteed!
name: Vol. 1

description: Yoshitsune finds himself chained up--literally--in an apartment! His latest client has imprisoned him so that she could have him all to herself. You see, she wants to take care of him...because Yoshitsune looks like her old dog!
name: Vol. 2

description: While the world is watching to see who's going to be the next top model of a trendy new fashion designer, Shima is behind the scenes becoming the next top detective! As Kaori competes against four other models for the top spot, he finds stiff competition from Shinku, a feisty elementary school kid model with a fast mouth and double personality. But when Kaori's waiting room gets trashed, it seems someone may have it in for him... Will Shima be able to stop the catwalk catastrophe?
name: Vol. 3

description: This volume of Satisfaction Guaranteed is a supernatural delight. Despite hating getting his fortune told, Shima has his Tarot read by an exotically handsome young man. But kismet turns into chaos when the reading isn't all wine and roses, and strange things start happening to Shima. Will he realize that a life of problem solving may not be in the stars?
name: Vol. 4

description: On their day off, Shima and Kaori find APP working in a sweets shop! But a sudden robbery ruins Shima's day off... In other cases, the two of them go on treasure hunts, deal with a potential younger sister, and neighborhood robbers while Shima also learns more about Kaori and Kyo, Kaori's alter-ego.
name: Vol. 5

description: It's back to the amusement park for Shima and his supermodel pal Kaori. They've been invited to test out a new attraction--a mystery-maze game. The dynamic duo is joined by old rivals Mai and APP, but along with them is a snooping reporter who wants to get the goods on Kaori. When Kaori collapses during the game, who will learn the secret of his other personality?
name: Vol. 6

description: On cases together, Shima and his supermodel pal Kaori have come to unconditionally trust one another. But suddenly, rival detective and sometimes friend Mai recalls a key piece of information about when she first met Kaori--and it was at the scene of Shima's parents' murder. Will searching for more information complete the puzzle, and if so, is the truth a picture they want to see?
name: Vol. 7

description: Lena Ha is a tough and beautiful girl who is also the captain of the Kendo team. Though skilled in swordplay, she is totally unprepared when she discovers that she has fallen in love--with her long-lost stepbrother! Unable to withstand her emotions, Lena runs away and has a near-death experience that takes her to a new world where her destiny is changed forever!
name: Vol. 1

description: Lena wakes up in a stange, distant world, where she's taken in by a mystic seer who thinks she is there to be the savior! As Lena learns more about her potential destiny, she journeys deep into the heart of this mystical land in order to unlock its secrets--and more. But when she's intercepted by the evil forces lurking in the shadows, her fate may be sealed for all eternity!
name: Vol. 2

description: Trapped in the Cave of Death, Lena and several men are suddenly released...to fight each other to the death as gladiators! Will Lena be able to use this to her advantage, escape her captors and free the others? Or will she meet her end before a bloodthirsty audience?
name: Vol. 3

description: The cave is crashing in, and Lena, Cid, Sean, the merchants and "The Great One" are all trapped inside--but with the leadership of Lena's male alter-ego, "Ley," they may have a chance to escape. If they make it out of the cave, it seems that something more terrifying awaits them at Glasgow Castle. Meanwhile, Lucien and Nox continue their search for "The Great One." What do they plan to do when they find him?
name: Vol. 4

description: Their new mission to locate and rescue Earl Romero from his evil nephew Chris is shaping up to be an easier task than they initially thought...or is it? Will the group be able to successfully finish their new quest so deep inside the heart of Chris's headquarter? And what about Edith? Will Ley be able to save the girl who loves her and finally shed her feeling of guilt, as she couldn't do the same for the one who loved Lena?
name: Vol. 5

description: When Ley and crew are captured by a bandit--who looks like Hyun-Min--they are taken to a town that’s surprisingly peaceful. Ley learns more about the bandit, who could possibly be her long-lost love from another time and place. However, peaceful days do not last as Yuriel leads his army to attack the town in his usual cruel fashion, killing men, women and even the children. Will Ley finally come face-to-face with the man who robbed her of people she loved?
name: Vol. 6

description: Haruhiko was born rich and grew up pampered. But when he can't take any more of his father's tyrannical behavior, he strikes out on his own, determined to make his own way in the world. But going from super-rich to super-poor is tough on any man (let alone one still in high school!), and it's going to take more hard work than Haruhiko imagined just to make ends meet. He's doing his best and trying to keep up his spirits, but living on bean sprouts and bread crusts is enough to get any man down. Fortunately, he's got his sexy classmates and his own personal (and very hot) maid to help him out!
name: Vol. 1

description: Fifteen years ago, a set of twins--a girl and a boy--was born to the king of Linevan. Shortly after their birth, a prophecy foretold that when the girl turned 16, she would bring about the end of humanity. To avoid this terrible fate, the king ordered the princess disposed of--scrapped! She miraculously survived and was raised away from the kingdom that would kill her. But now she has turned 15, the king's guards have caught wind that she's still alive...and they set out to finish the job!
name: Vol. 1

description: The epic sci-fi fantasy continues as the lives of everyone in the world hang in the balance! While Pacifica, Shannon, and Raquel flee from bounty hunters, Pacifica crosses paths with a frightened girl who has a dark secret and a fatal wish. After the girl disappears, a mysterious pendant might hold the clue to saving her. The three siblings set off to find the girl, but when they finally locate her, she's not quite what she appears to be...
name: Vol. 2

description: The four priests who predicted the "Revelation of Grendel" are found dead, and Tasa, one of the priest's daughters, now seeks revenge on Pacifica. In the midst of a punitive team attack on the siblings, Tasa and Raging Bull, a hired assassin, come to their aid because Tasa wants to kill Pacifica herself. Tasa and Pacifica end up getting captured. If they are rescued in time, will Tasa still want the blood of the "Destruction Princess?"
name: Vol. 3

Also: Norman Osborn sends the Sentry on a deadly mission!

Plus: The Secret and Dark Avengers are forced to team up when the frost giant Ymir invades Earth!

Collects

name: Cry Demon!
